14:53.060 --> 14:55.103
There's something
you should know about me.

14:59.441 --> 15:01.944
- Benji, are... are you okay?

15:03.278 --> 15:06.073
It's like you've barely said
a word since we left bingo.

15:08.825 --> 15:10.661
- Sorry.
- It's okay.

15:14.289 --> 15:15.791
- I just, uh...

15:17.334 --> 15:19.336
My dad pulled some strings...

15:20.379 --> 15:22.881
finally got my car accident
taken off my record.

15:23.924 --> 15:25.425
W-which I guess is...

15:27.010 --> 15:28.720
a good thing.

15:30.556 --> 15:32.558
It's just bringing up a lot of memories.

15:34.017 --> 15:35.102
- Yeah.

15:37.354 --> 15:39.481
- I didn't mean to make it heavy.

15:39.481 --> 15:41.525
- No, it-it's okay. I-I'm fine with heavy.

15:42.901 --> 15:45.320
I-I have so much I want to ask you.

15:45.320 --> 15:47.322
We never even talked about rehab.

15:50.367 --> 15:53.287
- Yeah. It was intense.

15:54.371 --> 15:55.873
But, good intense.

15:55.873 --> 15:57.207
[distant siren]

15:57.207 --> 16:00.210
I learned that I have...

16:00.210 --> 16:03.005
a lot of anxiety,
and drinking is how I cope.

16:03.839 --> 16:06.258
- You have anxiety? Dude, you're Benji.

16:06.258 --> 16:07.843
Nothing ever gets you.

16:09.678 --> 16:11.680
- Tricked ya.
[sighs]

16:14.683 --> 16:16.268
- What makes you anxious?

16:16.977 --> 16:18.604
- It's more like what doesn't.

16:20.731 --> 16:24.234
I just can't shake this feeling
that no matter what I do,

16:24.234 --> 16:27.237
I'm going to end up disappointing someone.

16:30.073 --> 16:31.575
- Well...

16:32.201 --> 16:34.995
y-you've never disappointed me.

16:34.995 --> 16:36.455
- Mm-hmm.
- Not once.

16:36.455 --> 16:38.457
- You're just saying that.

16:38.457 --> 16:40.459
- But, the thing is, like, I'm not.

16:46.632 --> 16:48.133
Look...

16:49.760 --> 16:51.762
I'm not trying to mess with your recovery.

16:53.722 --> 16:55.390
But...

16:55.390 --> 16:57.809
maybe us hanging out together

16:57.809 --> 16:59.269
could be good for you.

17:00.145 --> 17:02.856
As friends or as more than friends.

17:03.899 --> 17:05.776
Are you sure...

17:05.776 --> 17:08.445
that I-I'm one of the things
that you have to...

17:08.445 --> 17:09.988
stay away from?

17:09.988 --> 17:12.991
- Honestly, I don't know
what's good for me anymore.

17:14.159 --> 17:16.870
I'm just listening
to the experts and my parents,

17:17.829 --> 17:20.832
and they're telling me to keep my life

17:20.832 --> 17:23.836
as manageable and simple
as possible right now.

17:23.836 --> 17:26.421
♪

17:26.421 --> 17:29.925
And we are a lot of things, Victor.

17:32.511 --> 17:34.429
And I'm not sure simple is one of them.

17:37.808 --> 17:39.059
- Yeah.

17:39.601 --> 17:41.562
Yeah. Okay. I-I get it.

17:46.400 --> 17:48.402
- Good night, Victor.

17:55.117 --> 17:58.120
[insects chirping]
[quiet thud]

17:58.996 --> 17:59.705
[thud]

18:00.789 --> 18:02.374
[tapping]

18:07.546 --> 18:09.047
- What are you doing?

18:09.047 --> 18:10.716
If your parents found out you were here,

18:10.716 --> 18:12.718
we could be in serious trouble.

18:15.429 --> 18:17.264
- What they don't know won't hurt them.

18:21.185 --> 18:22.603
- W-what are you doing?

18:23.562 --> 18:25.439
- I just figured

18:25.439 --> 18:27.983
if we're going to be punished for it,

18:29.193 --> 18:30.611
we might as well do it.

18:31.737 --> 18:33.697
- Do...

18:33.697 --> 18:35.490
what... [awkward laugh]

18:36.200 --> 18:37.910
exactly?

18:41.830 --> 18:43.999
Mm. Mm. Wait, Pilar, wait.

18:43.999 --> 18:45.751
- Why? Is your mom home?

18:45.751 --> 18:48.837
- No. No, no, no, no, no.
Um, she's, uh, out with Stuart.

18:48.837 --> 18:51.089
I just-- You know, I'm not...

18:51.089 --> 18:52.132
Just not sure about this.

18:53.425 --> 18:55.135
- Well,

18:55.135 --> 18:57.429
maybe I can make you
a little more sure.

19:00.766 --> 19:03.685
- Wow. Uh, yeah, you are beautiful.

19:03.685 --> 19:04.686
[laughs]

19:06.355 --> 19:07.022
Mm...

19:08.357 --> 19:10.526
Wait-- Pilar, just stop.

19:10.526 --> 19:12.528
- What is your problem?
- Hey, hey. There's no problem.

19:12.528 --> 19:15.197
I just didn't picture
this being our first time.

19:15.781 --> 19:18.867
I just don't think we should be
having sex to spite your parents.

19:18.867 --> 19:20.661
- That's not what this is.

19:21.787 --> 19:22.788
I just...

19:22.788 --> 19:24.831
I feel you pulling away,

19:24.831 --> 19:27.125
and one minute, we're taking a step back.

19:27.125 --> 19:28.502
The next minute, we'll be breaking up.

19:28.502 --> 19:31.672
♪

19:31.672 --> 19:33.966
You seemed like you were excited
about having sex one day,

19:33.966 --> 19:35.509
so I thought if we did, it'd just...

19:36.552 --> 19:39.221
I just didn't want to lose you.
- Yeah, no. Pilar, you're not losing me.

19:39.221 --> 19:40.973
And I'm so excited. No. No, no, no.

19:40.973 --> 19:44.226
Hey, Pilar, can we please
just talk about this?

19:45.310 --> 19:46.812
[sighs]

19:52.734 --> 19:55.737
♪

20:00.784 --> 20:03.161
[sighs]

20:07.457 --> 20:09.459
- Okay, Benji, get some rest.

20:11.503 --> 20:14.506
We are just so glad to have you home.

20:16.008 --> 20:19.094
Okay. So get settled, and we'll
bring you something to eat.

20:19.928 --> 20:21.722
- Thanks.
- Okay.

20:21.722 --> 20:23.765
[door creaks]

20:24.349 --> 20:25.767
[sigh, grunting]

20:26.393 --> 20:27.895
CHARLES:
What are we gonna do?

20:28.478 --> 20:31.148
MARGARET: You need to do better.
He needs to feel your support.

20:31.148 --> 20:33.066
- I don't understand where we went wrong.

20:33.859 --> 20:37.279
MARGARET: We didn't go wrong.
Lots of people are gay,

20:37.279 --> 20:40.282
and they live wonderful, complete lives.
CHARLES: It's more than that.

20:40.282 --> 20:43.368
Who-who's this kid?
He's a terrible student.

20:43.368 --> 20:45.454
He's got a drinking problem.

20:45.913 --> 20:47.539
He's not the son I pictured.

20:47.539 --> 20:50.542
♪

20:53.170 --> 20:54.421
[knocking]

20:59.051 --> 21:01.970
- Mr. Campbell? Hey, wh-what's going on?

21:01.970 --> 21:03.764
- Hi, Victor.
I'm sorry to come by unannounced,

21:03.764 --> 21:06.099
but I was, um, hoping
you and I could talk.

21:06.475 --> 21:07.935
- Uh, yeah, sure. Come in.

21:07.935 --> 21:09.144
- This will only take a second.

21:09.144 --> 21:11.855
I saw you and Benji saying
good night outside of our house,

21:11.855 --> 21:14.900
and I'd really prefer
if you wouldn't see him anymore.

21:15.817 --> 21:17.152
- Uh...

21:17.152 --> 21:19.530
Look, I know everyone is
worried about him, but...

21:19.530 --> 21:20.948
- Worried?

21:21.865 --> 21:24.868
I wish I was worried. I'm terrified.

21:24.868 --> 21:26.662
♪

21:26.662 --> 21:29.540
My son almost died
in a drunk driving accident,

21:29.540 --> 21:32.835
and just a few months ago,
he was driving drunk again with you.

21:34.002 --> 21:36.713
The problems in your relationship
caused him to relapse.

21:37.589 --> 21:39.007
- We don't know that for sure.

21:40.968 --> 21:42.845
- All high school relationships
have their ups and downs,

21:42.845 --> 21:44.346
but you and Benji...

21:46.181 --> 21:48.725
Months of fighting.
And then, he-he sees you dancing

21:48.725 --> 21:52.062
with another boy at the wedding,
and he-he drives straight home

21:52.062 --> 21:53.272
to raid my liquor cabinet.

21:55.732 --> 21:58.735
I know you don't mean to,
but whenever you're around, you...

21:59.862 --> 22:02.322
[sighs] you create chaos.

22:05.284 --> 22:06.785
You're not good for him, Victor.

22:08.203 --> 22:10.622
And if you really cared about Benji,
you'd stay away.

22:10.622 --> 22:13.625
♪

22:19.631 --> 22:20.632
[knocking]

22:21.383 --> 22:22.759
- Hey.

22:24.261 --> 22:25.596
You okay?

22:25.929 --> 22:27.931
♪ We built a fire in the snow ♪

22:27.931 --> 22:28.974
- You?

22:29.975 --> 22:30.976
- No.

22:33.478 --> 22:36.732
- Felix needs Mom and Dad to be okay
with him more than he needs me.

22:38.984 --> 22:41.195
I know you're his best friend,
so you'll probably take the side.

22:41.195 --> 22:42.321
- You're my sister.

22:43.030 --> 22:45.032
I'll always have your back.
No matter what.

22:46.491 --> 22:47.910
♪ You have to sow the seed... ♪

22:47.910 --> 22:49.411
- Thank you.

22:50.162 --> 22:51.580
♪ And watch it grow ♪

22:51.580 --> 22:53.207
- What's up with you?

22:54.541 --> 22:56.460
♪ Everywhere I go,
all I ever see ... ♪

22:56.460 --> 22:57.961
- I...

22:59.087 --> 23:00.714
realized I'm bad for Benji.

23:01.882 --> 23:04.134
♪ People that I know
only ever speak ♪

23:04.134 --> 23:06.178
And I'll probably never be with him.

23:06.178 --> 23:09.056
♪ Like everything is heading
for catastrophe ♪

23:09.056 --> 23:10.140
♪ There's nothing I can do... ♪

23:10.140 --> 23:12.184
- Here. Have a fish.

23:12.976 --> 23:16.563
♪ Even if I could rewrite the history ♪

23:16.563 --> 23:18.273
♪ It's clear to see ♪

23:20.025 --> 23:22.027
♪ That I'd still be ♪

23:22.945 --> 23:24.530
♪ Loving ♪

23:24.530 --> 23:27.533
♪ You... ♪

23:30.327 --> 23:31.870
♪ Loving ♪

23:31.870 --> 23:34.873
♪ You ♪

23:37.709 --> 23:39.378
♪ Loving ♪

23:39.378 --> 23:42.381
♪ You... ♪

23:45.092 --> 23:48.887
♪ Loving you... ♪
